[normal]Written evidence submitted by WWF-UK[bold]&#xa0;[bold]INTRODUCTION[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]WWF is a leading global conservation organisation, employing over 5,000 staff in more than 100 countries 
[normal]and with more than 5 million supporte
[normal]rs across the world.  The UK charity
[normal] - WWF-U
[normal]K - was launched in 1961.  We are
[normal] a challenging, constructive, science-based organisation that addresses a wide range of issues including environmental and social best practic
[normal]e in the extractives sector.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We welcome the Business, Innovation and Skills 
[normal]Select 
[normal]Committee
[normal]’s timely Inquiry into the e
[normal]xtractives industry sector.
[normal] 
[normal] 
[normal]Our responses focus on those areas relevant to our work.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]RESPONSE[bold]S[bold] TO QUESTIONS[bold]&#xa0;[bold]What are the corporate governance concerns raised by the number of extractive industries companies listed in the UK?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Are there reputational risks for the UK and UK financi[bold]al institutions in being a centre for such businesses?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Is there sufficient engagement between UK extractive industries and the NGO sector?  Are there examples of best practice in engagement between the extractive industri[bold]es and NGOs? [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]What is the impact on [bold]the industry of the UK signing up to the EITI?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Would increased regulation for London listed extractives companies result in competition from elsewhere or can it be used to make the UK a centre of excellence for best practice and [bold]corporate governance?[bold]&#xa0;
